#compdef atomic-server
# =============================================================================
# atomic-server — Ontola / atomicdata-dev's "Create,
#                 share and model Atomic Data with this
#                 graph database server" — a Rust HTTP
#                 server implementing the Atomic Data
#                 protocol, a Joep Meindertsma-designed
#                 graph-data standard that combines RDF's
#                 triple-store data model with JSON-LD's
#                 modern JSON serialization, JSON Schema's
#                 validation semantics, and Solid's
#                 decentralized-web vision.  Atomic Data
#                 resources are first-class addressable
#                 URLs whose state is updated via signed
#                 Commits (event-sourcing pattern), with
#                 full version history retained,
#                 per-resource permissions, real-time
#                 WebSocket subscriptions, full-text
#                 search via tantivy, and bundled tabular
#                 + collection + drive abstractions.
#                 Distinguishing from Apache Jena
#                 (Java/Scala RDF triple store), Stardog
#                 (commercial RDF), Neo4j (property graph
#                 DB, not RDF), Solid Pod servers (PHP /
#                 Node.js implementations, less integrated
#                 search), Apache Solr / Elasticsearch
#                 (search engines without graph model),
#                 and AT Protocol PDS (decentralized data
#                 but no native search) by:
#                   - ATOMIC DATA PROTOCOL — Joep
#                     Meindertsma's spec (https://
#                     docs.atomicdata.dev/) that unifies
#                     RDF triples + JSON-LD serialization
#                     + JSON Schema validation +
#                     Commit-based event sourcing in a
#                     single coherent data model
#                   - TANTIVY FULL-TEXT SEARCH — uses
#                     paritytech-fork-derived quickwit-
#                     oss/tantivy for full-text search
#                     indexing (this is the headline CLI
#                     library that opens Axis 30; see
#                     taxonomy notes below)
#                   - ACTIX-WEB SERVER — uses Nikolay
#                     Kim's actix-web 4.x as the HTTP
#                     framework (Axis 26 covered
#                     transitively via tinacms's express
#                     usage)
#                   - LIBSODIUM-COMPATIBLE CRYPTO — uses
#                     ed25519 signatures for Commits +
#                     resource attribution
#                   - WEBSOCKETS FOR REAL-TIME SYNC —
#                     subscribers receive Commit
#                     notifications via WS; the front-
#                     end React SDK keeps UI in sync
#                     without polling
#                   - Y-SYNC INTEGRATION — bundled
#                     y_sync_broadcaster integrates with
#                     Yjs CRDTs (Kevin Jahns's Y.js) for
#                     conflict-free collaborative editing
#                     of resources
#                   - LETSENCRYPT AUTOMATIC HTTPS —
#                     `--https` flag enables automatic
#                     Let's Encrypt certificate provisioning;
#                     `--https-dns` supports DNS-01
#                     challenge for wildcard certs
#                   - JSON-AD IMPORT / EXPORT —
#                     `atomic-server export` + `atomic-
#                     server import` round-trip the
#                     entire store via JSON-AD (Atomic
#                     Data's canonical JSON serialization)
#                   - DOTENV CONFIG GENERATION — `atomic-
#                     server generate-dotenv` emits a
#                     .env file with all configurable
#                     options + defaults; helps with
#                     declarative deployments
#                   - OPENTELEMETRY TRACING — `--trace
#                     opentelemetry` sends traces to a
#                     local OTLP collector (e.g., Jaeger);
#                     `--trace chrome` writes Chrome
#                     Tracing-format JSON
#                   - HIERARCHICAL CONFIG — env-vars
#                     (ATOMIC_PORT, ATOMIC_HTTPS,
#                     ATOMIC_DATA_DIR) take precedence
#                     over CLI flags, which take precedence
#                     over defaults
#                   - PUBLIC MODE — `--public-mode`
#                     disables authentication for
#                     read-only public deployments
#                     (e.g., docs sites)
#                   - SLOW MODE — `--slow-mode` injects
#                     random delays; useful for testing
#                     UI loading states
#                 Used by: Atomic Data adopters building
#                 graph-data-backed applications, Solid-
#                 ecosystem developers wanting a server
#                 with built-in search + collaboration,
#                 researchers exploring federated +
#                 versioned data architectures, and
#                 European data-sovereignty initiatives
#                 (Joep Meindertsma's Dutch government +
#                 EU partnerships).
#
# Author:  Joep Meindertsma (joepio on GitHub) of
#          Ontola.io + atomicdata-dev community.  Project
#          previously under ontola/atomic-server,
#          recently migrated to atomicdata-dev org.
#          License: MIT.
# Source:  https://github.com/atomicdata-dev/atomic-server
#          https://github.com/ontola/atomic-server (older
#          location; some commits still appear here)
#          https://github.com/ontola/atomic-server/blob/main/server/src/config.rs
#          https://atomicdata.dev/
#          https://docs.atomicdata.dev/
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; documentation at
#          https://docs.atomicdata.dev/.
# Library: tantivy (Rust full-text search engine — the
#          headline dependency for this completion's
#          axis-opening role; see taxonomy notes below).
#          Also clap (Axis 1 argparse), actix-web (Axis 26
#          web framework), dialoguer (Axis 8 prompts),
#          colored (Axis 4 colors), dotenv (config),
#          regex (Axis 27-style), rio_api + rio_turtle
#          (RDF Turtle parsing), sanitize-filename, tracing
#          + tracing-actix-web (Axis 9 logging via tracing
#          crate), serde_with (advanced serde).
